* An inability to follow along with a speaker or provide adequate feedback to a speaker; and/or
* A refusal to ask for clarification or assistance from a speaker or colleague.

The above-listed behaviors are often indicative of someone who is pretending to understand or knowledgeable about a topic or conversation. This may be because they do not understand the topic or conversation or because they do not want to appear uninformed or unprepared.

The nth Fibonacci number can be found by performing dynamic programming. The following recursive function calculates the nth Fibonacci number:

\begin{code}
function fib(n) {
    if (n === 0 || n === 1) {
        return n;
    }

    const result = fib(n - 1) + fib(n - 2);

    return result;
}
\end{code}

The above function can be simplified by recursively calling the function with the current index being replaced by the previous index. This can be achieved by calling the function with `n - 1` instead of `n` and incrementing `n` by 1 each time. The following modified function has the same result as the original function, but is more concise.

\begin{code}
